choices.text:
trying to find my equilibrium. Family is very important here, so it’s very easy to be overwhelmed by guilt. Do I do this for my husband or this for my boss? How can I work and be a proper wife/mother and keep the family financially healthy?

I think that is a universal struggle. I feel like I am always balancing work/life/friends. It’s hard feeling pulled in so many different directions. I feel like some days I can do it all but others I slip up. I love JTBC’s What Is Wrong with Secretary Kim. What I love about Lee Young Joon and his secretary Kim Mi So is their relationship- that Ying & Yang in a relationship is so well-written in the drama. I do like dramas where the leads have an obvious love “hate” relationship. This drama has such good chemistry between the leads I could watch them get married and raise a kid- no problem!

I always struggle with my blog and trying to make real money from it- one day I feel like I have something I need to say the other I have nothing writer’s block is real!

A Happy New Year to you as well- K-Bops & K-Dramas will do a 2018 Year Review! Happy Reading and Writing. VeronikaKidnadske (sorry is reading the star sign causes confusion) But Love you! XOXOX Love & Luck to You!
